      • setUp

        protected abstract boolean setUp()
        Setups this plugin. This methods will be called for the initialization of this plugin after checking the required core version, and the dependences.

        Also this methods should return true if the initialization was successfully, and false if not. Returning false from this method means that the initialization was unsuccessfully, then the plugin will be disabled automatically.

        Returns:
        true if the initialization was successfully.

      • getRequiredCoreVersion

        public abstract CoreVersion getRequiredCoreVersion()
        Gets the required core version by this plugin. If the current core version is older than the required, the plugin will be disabled.

        Also this method might return null if no core version is required.

        Returns:
        The required core version, or null if not required.

      • getMetrics

      • getInternalLanguageContainer

        public abstract java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.Enum<? extends PluginInternalLanguageEnumContainer>> getInternalLanguageContainer()
        Returns the internal language enum container of this Plugin, or null if not implemented.

        The items of the given container will be loaded from the .lang resources that should be found at the given resources package. getInternalLanguageResourcesPackage().

        Returns:
        The language container of this Plugin, or null if not implemented.

      • setUpListenersPackage

        protected void setUpListenersPackage(java.lang.String packaje)
                              throws java.lang.InstantiationException,
                                     java.lang.IllegalAccessException,
                                     java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                     java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
        Loads all the listeners within the provided package.

        A listener within the provided package will be registered only when the following conditions are met:

        • The class implements the interface Listener.
        • The class is not abstract.
        • The class has a public constructor with the class of this plugin as parameter.
        In other case, the listener will be ignored.

        Implementation example:

        Plugin Class:

        
 public class MyPlugin extends Plugin { 
        
     ..... 
        
 }

        Listener Class:

        
 public class MyListener implements Listener { 
        

     public MyListener(MyPlugin plugin) { 
        
         Bukkit.getPluginManager().registerEvents(this, plugin); 
        
     } 
        
 }

        Parameters:
        packaje - The listeners package
        Throws:
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException - exception to handle
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - exception to handle
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - exception to handle
        java.lang.InstantiationException - exception to handle

      • saveResource

        public void saveResource(java.lang.String resource_path,
                         java.io.File out_directory,
                         boolean replace)
        Saves the raw contents of any resource embedded with this plugin's .jar file assuming it can be found using JavaPlugin.getResource(String).

        The resource is saved into the desired out_directory.

        Parameters:
        resource_path - The embedded resource path to look for within the plugin's .jar file. (No preceding slash).
        out_directory - The directory into which the resource will be saved.
        replace - If true, the embedded resource will overwrite the contents of an existing file.
